get

DynamicLibrary get(java.lang.String name)
Returns the DLL registered with the specified name/path (exactly, name is case sensitive), if it is not found tries to load the library from filesystem using the specified name/path.

The library name can optionally follow the rules of System.loadLibrary(String): a DLL file name without extension (.dll, .so or .dylib) and "lib" prefix (Linux/Mac/Solaris) or can be a normal path.

The loaded dynamic library is registered with the specified name.

The uniqueness of the DLL handle ensures only one DynamicLibrary instance is created per DLL but with multiple name registries.

If there is no DLL with this name/path an exception is thrown.

The specified name can be a native name expression as explained in NativeTypeManager.parseTextWithMacros(String), this method is internally called to get the name of the library to load.

Parameters:
name - used name/path to search.
Returns:
the DynamicLibrary object found or loaded.
See Also:
find(String)
